Protocol 1: Bandit Social Learning
Problem instance: two arms a [2] with (ﬁxed, but unknown) mean rewards µ1, µ2 [0, 1] ;
Initialization: hist { N0 samples of each arm };
for each round t = 1, 2, . . . , T do
agent t arrives, observes hist and chooses an arm at [2] ;
reward rt [ 0, 1 ] is drawn from Bernoulli distribution with mean µat;
new datapoint (at, rt) is added to hist
